project.name: Zeno Travel Domain v2
project.description:
An improved version of the Zeno travel domain from IPC3
The final transportation domain involves transporting people around in planes, using different modes of movement: fast and slow. The key to this domain is that, where the expressive power of the numeric tracks is used, the fast movement consumes fuel faster than slow movement, making the search for a good quality plan (one using less fuel) much harder.

actor.name: Person
actor.description: This agent can travel from a city to another by boarding in aircrafts.

useCase.name: Fly from one city to another
useCase.description: The aircraft fast from an origin city to a destination city.

definition.precondition: - the aircraft must be at the origin city; - there must be enough fuel in the aircraft, accordingly the aircraft slow burn and the distance between the two cities.
definition.postcondition: - the aircraft is at the destination city; - the fuel level is decreased.
definition.invariants: - no person boards in or debarks from the aircraft.

useCase.name: Fly fast (zoom) from one city to another

definition.postcondition: - the aircraft is at the destination city; - the fuel level is decreased.
definition.invariants: - no person boards in or debarks from the aircraft.

useCase.name: Board in an aircraft
useCase.description: The agent person boards in an aircraft at a city.

definition.precondition: - the person and the aircraft must be at the same city; - the aircraft current load must be lower than its capacity.
definition.postcondition: - the person is in the aircraft; - the aircraft load is increased.
definition.invariants: - the aircraft remains at the same city.

useCase.name: Debark from the aircraft
useCase.description: The agent person debarks from an aircraft at a city.

definition.precondition: - the aircraft must be at the city; - the person must be in the aircraft.
definition.postcondition: - the person is at the city; - the aircraft load is decreased.
definition.invariants: - the aircraft remains at the same city.

useCase.name: Total refuel
useCase.description: The agent aircraft is totally refueled at a fuel station wich is at a city.

definition.precondition: - the aircraft must be at the fuel station, which must be located at the city; - the aircraft must have less fuel than its fuel capacity.
definition.postcondition: - the fuel level is increased to the aircraft fuel capacity; - the fuel cost is increased accodingly to the amount of liters used and the fuel station price.
definition.invariants: - the aircraft remains at the fuel station; - no person boards in or debarks from the aircraft.

useCase.name: Partial refuel
useCase.description: The agent aircraft is partially refueled at a fuel station.

definition.precondition: - the aircraft must be at the fuel station, which must be located at the city; - the aircraft must have less fuel than its fuel capacity.
definition.postcondition: - the fuel level is increased; - the fuel cost is increased accodingly to the amount of liters used and the fuel station price.
definition.invariants: - the aircraft remains at the fuel station; - no person boards in or debarks from the aircraft.

action.precondition: a.at = c1 and c1 <> c2 and a.fuelLevel >= c1.distance(c2) * a.slowBurn
action.postcondition: a.at = c2 and a.fuelLevel = a.fuelLevel - c1.distance(c2) * a.slowBurn and flights = flights + 1

action.precondition: a.at = c1 and c1 <> c2 and a.fuelLevel >= c1.distance(c2) * a.fastBurn and a.onboard <= a.zoomLimit
action.postcondition: a.at = c2 and a.fuelLevel = a.fuelLevel - c1.distance(c2) * a.fastBurn and flights = flights + 1

action.precondition: a.fuelLevel < a.fuelCapacity and a.at = c and fs.belongsTo->includes(c)
action.postcondition: a.fuelLevel = a.fuelCapacity and totalFuelCost = totalFuelCost + (a.fuelCapacity - a.fuelLevel) * fs.fuelPrice

action.precondition: a.fuelLevel <= a.fuelCapacity - 2 and a.at = c and fs.belongsTo->includes(c)
action.postcondition: a.fuelLevel = a.fuelLevel + 2 and totalFuelCost = totalFuelCost + 2 * fs.fuelPrice

action.precondition: a.fuelLevel <= a.fuelCapacity - 5 and a.at = c and fs.belongsTo->includes(c)
action.postcondition: a.fuelLevel = a.fuelLevel + 5 and totalFuelCost = totalFuelCost + 5 * fs.fuelPrice

action.precondition: a.fuelLevel <= a.fuelCapacity - 10 and a.at = c and fs.belongsTo->includes(c)
action.postcondition: a.fuelLevel = a.fuelLevel + 10 and totalFuelCost = totalFuelCost + 10 * fs.fuelPrice
